Hi Guys i am trying to do something like this {% set all_dealers = crm_objects("company", "limit=200&amp;sales_group_en=E5&amp;sales_group_en=E4&amp;sales_group_en=E3"," sales_group_en, name, address, zip, city, country_key_en, website") %}
But it seems it only gets the results with the first sales_group_en property values (E5), the other ones (E4 and E3) are ignored
Is there a better way to query the all_dealers? I was also wondering is there a way you can use your named view (with all it's filter settings) as a selector in some way to get the same results through a query like this?
